room_title: Escape room "Dracula" by Quest Factor in Seattle
review: It's a three room.  You go to a room find a way to another and then third one opens..  Mostly opening coffins.  It's well designed but mostly easy if you pay attention

room_title: Escape room "Dracula" by Quest Factor in Seattle
review: Today I did the Dracula Room in Redmond with 3 other people. This is the 4th escape room my husband and I have done -- all at different companies. Quest Factor is by far our favorite/the best one we've done. The d√©cor was amazing and the puzzles were interesting and varied. They also ALL worked. (Two other places had broken puzzles, and another basically only had the same kind of puzzle repeated over and over, so not very fun.) I would definitely recommend this place and plan to go back.

room_title: Escape room "Dracula" by Quest Factor in Seattle
review: SO MUCH FUN! The puzzles are unique and you gotta be creative with your thinking! I recommend the Dracula room! Not scary but still challenging

room_title: Escape room "Dracula" by Quest Factor in Seattle
review: We booked the Dracula room at the Redmond location and it was very atmospheric and enjoyable! Great ambiance in the room and challenging puzzles! We will definitely come back and try another room.
